-- Taiwan Equity Movers: Cathay Financial, Fubon Financial, SinoPac
-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 2011-12-22T06:21:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/taiwan-equity-movers-cathay-financial-fubon-sinopac-nanya.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index was little changed at 6,966.35. The gauge
has dropped 22 percent this year.  Financial shares:  Cathay Financial Holding Co. (2882)  (2882 TT)
surged 4 percent to NT$31.15, the highest close since Dec. 12.
 Fubon Financial Holding Co. (2881)  (2881 TT) gained 2.2 percent to
NT$30.60.  SinoPac Financial Holdings Co. (2890)  (2890 TT) rallied 6.4
percent to NT$9.20, closing at the highest level since Dec. 5.  The TWSE Financial and Insurance Industry Index  advanced
1.9 percent, rising for a second day after the Financial
Supervisory Commission said it will let Chinese banks buy stakes
in local lenders and financial holding companies from Jan. 2.  Chinatrust Financial Holding Co. (2891)  (2891 TT) jumped 4.9
percent to NT$18.35. Chinatrust Commercial Bank sold NT$880
million ($29 million) of loan assets to China Development
Industrial Bank, parent Chinatrust Financial said in a statement
to the Taiwan stock exchange yesterday. China Development
Industrial is a subsidiary of  China Development Financial
Holding Corp.  (2883 TT). Shares of China Development Financial
added 1.6 percent to NT$8.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adela Lin in Taipei at 
 alin95@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
